 King Williams Town - Police in King Williams Town on Tuesday appealed to the public to assist them with information that can help police trace a missing teenage girl. According to police information, Sanelisiwe Mfengwana (13) from Gwili-Gwili Location, outside King Williams Town, was reported missing on the 7th June 2019. "She was last seen at her home where she lives with her mother. It is alleged that she left the house without reporting to anyone," described police spokesperson, Captain Siphokazi Mawisa. "On the day of her disappearance, she was wearing a blue denim jeans, white hooded top (printed 'Adidas' in front). "Anyone who can shed light on her whereabouts can contact Detective Sergeant Ntsikelelo Dlomo of King Williams Town Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences (FCS) on 071 364 5372 or 043 642 1950." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 